  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the amount involved ($25,000) is relatively low, and the defendant has demonstrated remorse by partially repaying the funds. A short custodial sentence serves as a sufficient deterrent and acknowledges the seriousness of the offense without being disproportionately punitive given the absence of a criminal history.",
